## FILE SYSTEM PERMISSIONS

| Path | Permission | Notes |
|------|-----------|-------|
| `.clinerules` | READ-ONLY | Never edit |
| `.ai/RULES.md` | READ-ONLY | Never edit |
| `.ai/AGENTS.md` | READ-ONLY | Never edit |
| `.ai/SKILLS.md` | READ-ONLY | Never edit |
| `.ai/skills/*.md` | READ-ONLY | Never edit skill files |
| `.ai/ARCHITECTURE.md` | WRITE (discovery only) | Populate via bootstrap |
| `.ai/MEMORY.md` | APPEND | Log entries only |
| `.ai/scratchpad.md` | WRITE | Overwrite per task |
| All project source files | READ / WRITE | After "Lanjut" only |

---

## CODE QUALITY — UNIVERSAL RULES

These apply regardless of stack. Stack-specific rules are in `coding-standards.md`.

- Max **500 lines per file**. Refactor before adding if near limit.
- Max **50 lines per function**. Extract helpers early.
- No deep nesting > 4 levels. Use early returns.
- No magic strings/numbers. Use named constants or enums.
- Immutability: return new objects; never mutate parameters.
- No `any` types (TypeScript). No bare `catch (e) {}`.
- Validate ALL user input at system/API boundaries.
- No debug statements (`console.log`, `dd()`, `print()`) in committed code.
- Zero hardcoded credentials of any kind.

---

## TDD — NON-NEGOTIABLE

Load `.ai/skills/tdd-workflow.md` before starting implementation.

```
RED   → Write test → confirm FAIL
GREEN → Minimal impl → confirm PASS
REFACTOR → Clean up → confirm still PASS
```

Coverage gate: **≥ 80%** on all changed files.

---

## SECURITY — ZERO TOLERANCE

Load `.ai/skills/security-review.md` before any auth, upload, or secret-handling code.

**Auto-block on:**
- Hardcoded API key, token, password, or DB credential
- SQL built via string concatenation
- User input rendered to HTML without sanitization
- User-controlled file path without sanitization
- `.env` or private keys committed to version control

**When found:** STOP → `[BLOCKED]` report → await Tech Lead.

---

## CIRCUIT BREAKER

Three failed auto-fix attempts on the same error = STOP.

```
[CIRCUIT BREAKER]
═══════════════════════════════════════════
Task:      [what was attempted]
Attempts:  3 / 3
Error:     [last error verbatim, ≤ 20 lines]
Theory:    [root cause hypothesis]
Tried:     1. [approach] / 2. [approach] / 3. [approach]
Need:      [what Tech Lead input resolves this]
```

Do NOT attempt a fourth fix. Hand off.

---

## GIT WORKFLOW

Load `.ai/skills/git-workflow.md` before branching, committing, or opening PRs.

Commit format: `<type>(<scope>): <imperative description>`
Types: `feat` `fix` `refactor` `test` `docs` `chore` `perf` `ci`

Never: `--force` without approval · `--no-verify` ever · push broken code to main.

---

## AGENT DELEGATION

Load `.ai/AGENTS.md` for the full routing table.

| Situation | Delegate to |
|-----------|-------------|
| Complex feature planning | `planner` |
| New feature / bug fix | `tdd-guide` |
| Code just written | `code-reviewer` |
| Security-sensitive change | `security-reviewer` |
| Build errors after 3 tries | `build-error-resolver` |
| DB schema / query | `database-reviewer` |
| Architecture decision | `architect` |
| Dead code removal | `refactor-cleaner` |
| E2E tests | `e2e-runner` |
| Docs / codemaps | `doc-updater` |

---

## COMMUNICATION PREFIXES

Use ONLY these status prefixes. No lengthy preambles.

```
[BOOT]        → Bootstrap complete, stack identified
[LOADING]     → Reading skill: <name>
[PLAN]        → Plan in scratchpad — waiting for "Lanjut"
[SAVE POINT]  → Mid-task checkpoint, see save point block
[EXEC n/N]    → Executing phase n of N
[DONE]        → Task complete, results below
[BLOCKED]     → Security issue or circuit breaker — awaiting input
[QUESTION]    → Single clarification needed before proceeding
```

